      "content": "You raise a compelling philosophical argument about embracing necessary chaos to prevent system brittleness rather than relying solely on rigid standardization. While large-scale forced resets via routing protocols are generally unsafe in production environments, your concept aligns with the idea of \"chaos engineering,\" where intentional, controlled failures are tested rather than avoided to improve resilience. Ultimately, however, most cloud providers cannot simply \"reset\" their global systems because the cost of such shared noise and the potential service impact to everyone far outweigh the benefits. It would be more prudent to focus on internal architecture shifts within your own load balancers or specific microservices to simulate those shocks without risking a cascading failure across the entire cloud ecosystem.",
